# RDS backups & PITR

## Two mechanisms, always running

- **Automated backups** (default) — daily snapshot + **tx logs → S3 every 5 min**, retained **1–35 days**
  - → **Point-in-time restore** to any second (snapshot base + log replay)
  - **Tied to the instance** — deleted with it (unless a final snapshot)
- **Manual snapshots** — you / automation trigger; **persist until deleted**
  - **Copy cross-region** (DR) · **share to accounts** (re-encrypt)

## The rule

**Restore always creates a NEW instance** — PITR doesn't rewind in place. *(Aurora Backtrack does — later.)*

**Automated + PITR** = undo recent hours · **manual snapshots** = long-term / DR / sharing.
